1 L.D. 606
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Clerk of the House.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 374, L.D. 606, “Resolve, to Study
10 Barriers to Financial Assistance Programs for Farmers and Food Producers”
11 Amend the resolve by inserting before section 1 the following:
12 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
13 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
14 Whereas, farmers and food producers are facing increasing challenges when trying
15 to access both state and federal grant programs; and
16 Whereas, this legislation needs to take effect before the expiration of the 90-day
17 period to allow the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Bureau of
18 Agriculture, Food and Rural Resources to study the bureau's financial assistance programs
19 to identify barriers to and improve effectiveness of these programs as soon as possible; and
20 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
21 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
22 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
23 therefore, be it'
24 Amend the resolve by adding before the summary the following:
25 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
26 takes effect when approved.'
27 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
28 section number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment adds an emergency preamble and an emergency clause to the resolve.
3311 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3322 (See attached)
